  "local_port": 58042,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What's the best applicant tracking system for a small staffing agency?",
  "response": "Choosing the best applicant tracking system (ATS) for a small staffing agency depends on several factors, including budget, ease of use, features required, scalability, and customer support. Here are some highly recommended ATS options for small staffing agencies:\n\n1. **Breezy HR**:\n   - **Pros**: User-friendly, affordable, good candidate management tools, customizable workflows, and integrates with various job boards.\n   - **Cons**: Limited reporting features\n\n2. **JazzHR**:\n   - **Pros**: Cost-effective, customizable pipelines, extensive integrations, and strong collaborative features.\n   - **Cons**: Can get pricey with additional features and integrations.\n\n3. **Workable**:\n   - **Pros**: Intuitive interface, robust sourcing tools, good candidate management, and extensive integrations.\n   - **Cons**: Higher cost compared to others, limited customization in workflow.\n\n4. **Zoho Recruit**:\n   - **Pros**: Affordable, good for staffing agencies, customizable, strong reporting features, and integrates well with Zoho's suite.\n   - **Cons**: Can be complex to navigate for new users.\n\n5. **Lever**:\n   - **Pros**: Great user experience, strong collaboration features, integrated CRM, excellent reporting and analytics.\n   - **Cons**: Can be expensive for small agencies.\n\n6. **Bullhorn**:\n   - **Pros**: Specifically designed for recruitment agencies, comprehensive CRM integration, scalable, strong automation features.\n   - **Cons**: Higher cost, can be complex to implement and navigate.\n\n7. **Recruitee**:\n   - **Pros**: Modern interface, affordable, strong collaborative features, customizable pipelines, and good integration options.\n   - **Cons**: Limited advanced reporting features.\n\nEach staffing agency has unique requirements, so it's important to evaluate each option based on your specific needs. Consider factors like ease of use, integration capabilities, customer service, scalability, and pricing structure. Most ATS providers offer demo versions or trial periods, so take advantage of these to test the systems before making a decision.",
